We should use a global `.gitignore` to avoid committing unnecessary files into our Git repositories.

Our repository `.gitignore` should only contain a list of the specific files generated within that project which should be ignored for that particular repository.

https://sebastiandedeyne.com/setting-up-a-global-gitignore-file/

Example global `.gitignore` file:
https://github.com/hanchang/dotfiles/blob/master/.gitignore
